properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 5:53PM AKST until January 11 at 5:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow and snow. Additional snow accumulations of 2
to 4 inches. East to northeast winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Kuskokwim Delta Coast and Nunivak Island. Pockets of
blowing snow will move inland, but visibilities will not drop
as low as coastal areas.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM AKST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility to one half mile or
less at times. The dangerously cold wind chills as low as 30
below zero could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as
10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The worse conditions will continue through
the evening before conditions slowly improve after midnight.
properties.instruction: Slow down and use caution while traveling.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM AKST SATURDAY ALONG THE COAST OF THE KUSKOKWIM DELTA
